Selected, mixed & presented by yours truly, Lars Behrenroth 

Featuring music by the likes of Ron Trent, Blaze, DJ Gregory, Osunlade, Earth People, Trackheadz, Omniverse, Soldiers of Twilight, and many more ..

Download, podcast, playlist, and more at https://www.deepershades.net/800

Happy Holidays and Merry Christmas from the Behrenroth’s ;)

We hope you’ll get to spend some quality time with your loved ones ..

I finally got a few days to chill before I’ll be back live on Wednesday to record my last mix for this year (don’t forget, Atjazz is closing out the last DSOH show for 2022 !!!)

Look what Santa (aka my wife Kathy;) got me for Christmas !!!
 
First use will be on NYE … I’m super excited .. thank you my love ..

Thank you all for an amazing year 2022 .. to be able to celebrate the 20 year anniversary of my weekly “Deeper Shades Of House” radio show and podcast with many of you, either through the broadcasts, or even in person at my gigs, was a very memorable experience. 
 
Thank you to all who attended, downloaded, listened, subscribed, thank you to all the DSOH premium members, thank you to the guest DJs, and to the labels and artists for all the super music !!! 

The last show of the year, #DSOH 802, features a bit of a “Best Of 2022” special, as well as an exclusive guest mix by ATJAZZ from the UK (for the first time ever on DSOH) …
 
THANK YOU,
Lars Behrenroth 

#20yearsDSOH #DSOH4LIFE #OnlyGoodMusic #RealDeephouse

Yooooo. The list is long..

Wow. The comments just keep coming. We’re almost at 800 ..

Safe to say that DSOH has been having quite an impact … 

#DSOH4LIFE

2023 marks the 15-year anniversary of Lars Behrenroth's record label Deeper Shades Recordings. What better way to start out this year of new releases than with a heavy track by the man himself? 

Lars Behrenroth “Perspective”

For the third time, the Deeper Shades Of House community got involved. 
 
DSOH Premium Platinum member Tristan Belfield from Melbourne, Australia is the executive producer of this Lars Behrenroth release on Deeper Shades Recordings. 

Tristan's contribution made this release happen and unlocked the opportunity for everyone else to download it for free via our Bandcamp page at https://deepershades.net/perspective

If you decide, you can also contribute by entering any amount you'd like in the 'Name Your Price' box 🙂 

I appreciate you all and am excited about what 2023 is gonna bring for Deeper Shades Recordings. Let's take a ride .. 

Keep It Deep,
Lars Behrenroth

Join us at www.twitch.tv/deepershadesofhouse 
#deephouselovers #larryheard #musicstreamer #realdeephouse #dsoh4life

I unfortunately never met AKA :( 
Just a few months someone sent me his story, playing my song “Minority In Terms Of Thought” in his car. #RIPAAKA

The moral of the story? 
“Don’t mess with the decks when someone else is playing” !!!

😂

Look what just arrived from Focusrite !!! A brand new Clarett+ 4Pre

My time for a new soundcard is overdue, I can’t even update my MacOS with what I’m currently using.
 
I can’t wait to hear how the Clarett+ improves the sound of my recordings, radio shows, live broadcasts, and more .. 

Hopefully I’ll find the time to hook it up this weekend. I’ll keep you updated…

#soundcard #goodsound #focusriteclarett #focusrite #deephouseproducer #livebroadcaster

Respect the equipment !!!
Especially when it’s not yours :)

The first mix from @deepershadesofhouse radio show 809. 
Byron the Aquarius “Fallenquas” into Shakez Von Nigo “Who Are We” 
 
You can check the full show at www.deepershades.net/809 ..

… and, we’re up and running. 
I’ve replaced my old interface with a brand new Focusrite Clarett+ 4Pre …
 
For now I have my main out in the front inputs since I needed some more volume to record and stream .. next experiments will involve my mic going directly into the Clarett+ instead of the Mackie mixer. I’m super excited to hear the preamp. 

Side note, who remembers all the other gear in the rack? :) 
I’m so tempted to hook up my ESI-32 and JV-2080 which are still in a crate in a corner .. 

maybe when I find time ;)

Check the full tunes on my newest show DSOH 809 at www.deepershades.net/809

Please join me in wishing a Happy Birthday to the love of my life, my anchor, and my everything, Kathy !!!

New York City has been so much fun. We got to explore some parts of Brooklyn yesterday but have to come back soon to check out all the record stores. They’re all spread out pretty far ..
 
We got 11 more hours today before our flight leaves back to LA ;)

#familytrip #familyaboveall

Shout out to my man Jun for asking me to join him last night to pick and play records at Peanut Butter Wolf’s Gold Line Bar.
 
DJs are not allowed to bring their own records and must pick all that’s played from PBW’s collection which is on the shelves all over the place. 

It’s a super fun concept, and truly amazing to dig through his collection and find a lot of gems ..
Tell me it’s a lie ..

Family trip ;)

#springbreak #familyaboveall

We made it to Japan :)
#familytrip #familyaboveall

Happy Birthday to our son Mattias. 
You’re growing into an amazing young man with a very pure heart. 
 
Side note, I’m terrified of heights, but every year he asks us to go on taller and taller buildings lol. 
Yesterday we went up 450m to the top platform of the Tokyo Sky Tree. Eeeek ;)
Seeing how excited and happy he gets, makes me forget all about my fears.

Look at these speakers at The Bridge in Tokyo !!! 

It sounds so amazing in this room, plus it’s on the tenth floor overlooking Shibuya Crossing ..

 I wouldn’t mind playing at this venue someday ..

Special 50th anniversary edition of the Technics SL-1200 turntable at Tower Records in Tokyo .. 

I bought my first SL-1210 back in 1988 (‘89) and it’s still mint ;) thinking about it, I should bring both of my 1210s back to the US when I’m visiting my mom in Germany next month. 
Or, I’ll just sell them since I already have two 1200s @ Deeper Shades HQ ..

Thank you all so much for the birthday wishes. I really appreciate all the messages, comments, texts, and phone calls. 

This is the second time Mattias and I got to celebrate our birthdays in Japan, and it won’t be the last. However, next time we need to stay more than a week. There is sooooo much to do and to see.

We’re still in Kyoto until tomorrow when we’re flying back to the crazy US of A. Each time I’m out of the country I realize all the things that are wrong with it even more than usual. But that’s a whole other conversation.
 
Wednesday I’ll be live again, and Friday I’ll have a new episode of Deeper Shades Of House ready for you all!
 
Btw. the hoodie I’m wearing is available in the Deeper Shades online shop.
They really have to stop taking pictures of me when I’m DJing … tzztzz

My next gigs ..
 
May 7th _ DJOON, Paris France
May 12th _ Grow Hackney, London UK
May 13th _ We Turn Tables, Limerick Ireland

Floating above Tokyo was one of my favorite things we did. 😂 

Kintoun ftw

In a few days I’m heading to Germany to hang out with my mom and go through some 1000+ vinyl records I still have in the basement over there ;)
 
While I’m that side, I’m gonna play some gigs as well. 

First one will be Djoon in Paris on Sunday, May 7th (I’m gonna post the flyer as soon as I get it) 

On my way back home to the US, I’ll be in London on Friday, May 12th for the first time in many years. Join me at Grow Hackney with Matt & Jamesey of Makin’ Moves and Laroye !!! 

On Saturday, May 13th, I will be in Limerick, Ireland to play at “We Turn Tables” (I’m gonna post that flyer next ;) 
 
I hope to see you at these parties if you’re in the area ..

Sunday, May 7th, I’ll be at Djoon in Paris, France to play alongside these two fine gentlemen, Kapela and Rocco Rodamaal ..
Doors open at 10pm and the party goes til 6am .. 

A week later, I’ll be at Grow Hackney in London, UK (May 12th), and We Turn Tables in Limerick, Ireland (May 13th) ..
 
It’d be great to see you at one of these if you’re in the area !!!

“If You Can’t Dance, You Should At Least Be Able To Do A Happy Hop” 

Music for this action could be provided by my weekly “Deeper Shades Of House” radio show, OR you could come out to one of my upcoming gigs !!! 
 

May 7th - DJOON - Paris, France
May 12th - Grow Hackney - London, UK
May 13th - We Turn Tables - Limerick, Ireland
June 9th - Dante's Hifi - Austin, Texas
June 10th - Dante's Hifi - Miami, Florida
June 11th - tba - St.Petersburg, Florida

Btw, I took this photo during our last trip to Kyoto, Japan ;)

I love puffer fish !!!

Took this video at the Sumida Aquarium in Tokyo ..

I’ve been going through some pictures with my mommy :)

Here’s a throwback from 29 years ago. 

Look at the modems on the right, and tell me where you think I connected to?!? ;)
“Get away from me” 😂

I was always a selector and provider of music ;) 

This photo was taken at my mom’s wedding when I was almost 8 years old ..
 
The Uher reel 2 reel is still in her basement.

Happy Mother’s Day to the two most important women in my life. My mom Marie-Luise, and my wife Kathy !!!
 
I wouldn’t be who I am without you in my life and seeing and feeling how much you love your sons is everything to me. 

I love you 💕😘❤️

This has been a trip loaded with travel, much of which forced me to leave the house at 3am. But in the end it was all worth it. 

My gig on Friday in London was super, and Saturday in Limerick was absolutely epic. 
It’s been way too long since I got to play four hours in an underground setting only to leave the place when the sun was already out !!! 

I’ll be taking things a bit slower once I’m back home to catch up on my sleep ;)

However, I’ll be live in the mix on Wednesday to record for DSOH show 819, dropping on Friday !!!
 
Next layover, Amsterdam, for the fifth time in the last two weeks, and then I’m heading home to LA ;)

My newest tune “Nothing” is now available on all digital platforms to stream and download ..
 
This one features my voice and own lyrics for the first time ;) no worries, I’m not singing 😂 

If you’re a creator of any kind, you might be able to relate to what I’m taking about in the song ..
 
As always, DSOH Premium members can download it for free from the Deeper Shades website thanks to DSOH Premium Platinum member Ricky Jones Jr.. 
 
Ricky unlocked this release and became the executive producer when he signed up as a Platinum supporter. 

www.deepershades.net/nothing
Happy Pride Month !!

It’s been a while since I played last in St.Petersburg, Florida. I’m excited to be back on Sunday, June 11th  alongside Austen van der Bleek and John Velez !!!
 
The days before you can catch me play vinyl at Dante’s Hifi in Austin, Texas (on Fri, June 9th) and Dante’s Hifi in Miami, Florida (on Sat, June 10th) 

See you there ;)

“Deepness has to come natural”
If you haven’t yet, please check out my newest release, “Nothing” and grab one of these DSOH mugs :)
 
www.deepershades.net/nothing

I’m so excited for this weekend’s gigs that I have been going through my vinyl for a week now ;)
 
Catch me in the mix at both Dante’s Hifi locations. 

First in Austin, Tx alongside JT Donaldson on Friday, June 9th and then in Miami, Florida with Dvize on Saturday, June 10th ..
 
Then I’m taking a train! to St.Petersburg, Florida to play at The Catalyst in Deuces Corner on Sunday, June 11th !!! (Flyer’s already on my timeline)

Dante’s Hifi in Miami was soooo much fun last night. Dvize laid down some serious tunes and after I played for three hours we ended up playing b2b and still dropped some more for the staff after closing .. what a vibe. 

Thank you to all who came out. I met quite a few veteran DSOH listeners last night who’ve been listening for 15 years and longer !!! 

Now I’m on the train for 5+ hrs to Tampa to play in St.Petersburg later today .. 

I’m on at 8pm at The Catalyst / Deuces Corner ..

Thank you Austen van der Bleek for making last night happen in St.Petersburg, Florida. Shout out  also to John Velez for laying down tunes and to everyone who came out. Again, plenty of longtime listeners came out to say hello. I appreciate you all !! 

Thanks to my man Jask for the pics .. I hadn’t seen him in years. 

This weekend was amazing. Three nights, three cities, three gigs, all vinyl !!! 

I need to do more of these trips. Anyone want to book me ? ;) 

Now I’m heading back home to Redondo Beach ..

Talk about timing. Right when I got home last night and took this UDG bag out of the trunk of the car, the handle broke when trying to roll it inside !!! I’ve had this sucker for over 20 years. It was a good run .. 

Should I get a new one of these, or is there anything better these days? They’re quite expensive to buy state side as well .. 

It needs to be a trolley / roller bag since I’ve been bit again by the vinyl gig bug and want to play more of those while being able to carry on and not having to check the bag when flying.. 

Please let me know.
Wuuaaahaaahaaaa

social_posts.post_text: There are many fun aspects of traveling to South Africa every year. One of them is seeing longtime friends, and even better, playing alongside them ..

I am always Rocco Rodamaal’s fan, but tonight I am watching him while sitting right behind him on stage ;)
 
We’ll both see you all tomorrow at the DSS Music & Lifestyle Festival in Johannesburg and the Drakensberg Extravaganza in Bergville. I hope you got your ticket …

Yesterday’s Deep Soul Sensation event was outstanding. I had so much fun that I only took this video after playing my last track …. 
Thank you DJ Christos and Lady Sakhe for making this happen and thank you to everyone who coming out .. what a great day with my South African family ..

Now I’m on my way to Eswatini for my gig at Sundeck Manzini tonight …

Right now I’m on my way to Eswatini for my gig at Sundeck Manzini tonight .. 
I’ll be on from 21:00 to 23:00 followed by my man Slotta !!! 

DSOH merchandise will be available for sale while I’m there ..

Thank you House Musiq Fest in Eswatini. 

Shout out to everyone involved in making it happen and everyone who partied with us … special shout out to Slotta who played a killer set right after me .. 

I recorded my set btw.
If it came out well, I’ll play one hour of it on the new Deeper Shades Of House show dropping on Friday !!!

Im very happy I got to chill with my extended family before our flights back home tonight …

This was an action packed weekend filled with love and amazing music. 

As always, DJ Christos and Lady Sakhe made sure everything went smoothly !! Thank you for all you do for us, but most importantly for the culture ..
 
It was super to hang with Martin Atjazz and my brother from another mother, Rocco Rodamaal .. 

Martin asked me a few times me to make more music and I am super motivated to say the least … 

Thank you to all who attended our gigs and showed your love either on the dancefloor or in person while having little chats and while taking pictures (I know, I said no to quite a few of you, but when chowing on ribs, I don’t like to take pictures lol)

Until next time my South African Deeper Shades family. I can’t wait to be back ..

I said it last year, and this year just proved me right. Deep Soul Sensation does some of the best events in South Africa !!!
 
Great people, great music, great vibes. 

Thank you all who came out to this year’s DSS Music & Lifestyle Festival. I feel honored to have been part of this event. 

Shout out to Tudups for the photos ..

Please let them know ;)
